# Full Stack Pre-Work Instructions
Make sure you read all steps of instructions thoroughly and complete all steps.<br><br>
### Application
Please go [HERE](https://savvycoders.com/apply-now-form/) to apply to
our program<br>

1. Register for our next Preview/Crash Course
Free 2 hour course, an overview of our program: [HERE](https://www.eventbrite.com/o/savvy-coders-8391701576)<br><br>
2. Documents & Information
Fill out this form entirely. Complete this form: [HERE](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc2b-ehrCLOn5ppo8u8d7aDlXBDadduG6QrmJQLV-8LcUlqVw/viewform)<br><br>
3. Pre-Work [(Google form)](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScQ5lGboNFEGcbgcB3Zq9mYrfAAVkn-PqFh67iQuOxiS7s3UQ/viewform)
- Go to each of the links below and complete each of the courses.
  - Make sure you practice time management and pace yourself with
this pre-work. There is a lot to do so use your time efficiently.
- Fill out [this form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScQ5lGboNFEGcbgcB3Zq9mYrfAAVkn-PqFh67iQuOxiS7s3UQ/viewform) as you work through the pre-work to provide us with
progress updates and screenshots.
  - The sites will give you a "badge" (badge/proof of
completion/results) once you have completed the course, fill out the
Google form accordingly & upload a screenshot of the badge.<br>
<h3 align="center"><b>***Start with JavaScript it’s the longest!***</b></h3>

- Free Code Camp
Please go to this site for the JavaScript prerequisite:
https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/
- Go to the JavaScript Algorithms & Data Structures
Then do both:
  1. Basic JavaScript
  2. ES6
- Code Academy
  - DO NOT ACCEPT THE FREE TRIAL of “Pro” FOR CODE
ACADEMY
  - Three courses in Code Academy. It's a way to get you exposed as
well as make sure you are serious and want to follow through with
this program.
    1. [Introduction to HTML](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-html)
    2. [Learn CSS](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-css)
    3. [Make a Website](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/make-a-website)

- GIT
  - [Free Code Camp: Learn Git](https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/what-is-github-what-is-git-and-how-to-use-these-developer-tools/)
- Git Bash
  - A short YouTube video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oQc-2gsjgDg
  - 2 articles:
    1. https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/understanding-git-basics-com
mands-tips-tricks/
    2. https://dzone.com/articles/top-20-git-commands-with-examples
    <br><br>

4. Meetup
- You are required to attend 2 "tech" meetups by the time of graduation and send
an email with information about the ones you attended. Please go to as many as
you can between now and the start of the course, this is an excellent way for you
to network.
- You can find a list of tech-related meetups [HERE](https://www.meetup.com/find/?keywords=coding&location=us--mo--Saint%20Louis&source=EVENTS&distance=fiftyMiles)
  - Several have gone virtual, there are a lot out there, please do your
best.
- Submit progress update with this [Google form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScQ5lGboNFEGcbgcB3Zq9mYrfAAVkn-PqFh67iQuOxiS7s3UQ/viewform).
<br><br>

5. Typing Test
- You will need to pass a typing test; at 40wpm, [this is the one I use](https://www.typingtest.com/) so you
can practice if you need to.
- The link to the test I use is HERE
- Upload results to this [Google form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScQ5lGboNFEGcbgcB3Zq9mYrfAAVkn-PqFh67iQuOxiS7s3UQ/viewform).
<br><br>

6. Review the attached Agile Document.
<br><br>

7. Funding:
- LETC Funding
  - If you intend to be Funded in Missouri please complete the
following ASAP and let me know about it.
    - Go to [jobs.mo.gov](https://jobs.mo.gov/)
    - Go to Login and Registration Options
    - Create an Individual Account or log in to your account
    - Update it with accurate information
    - Make sure ALL contact information is in there.
  - Follow the instructions laid out here [Talify](https://jobs.mo.gov/sites/jobs/files/talify_-_seeker_tip_061418.pdf)
    - Take the Talify Test
    - Once Talify test is done, forward the Talify
confirmation email that they send you
  - Email Derek to let him know you are done!
- Loan Info:
  - If you want to apply for a Loan through the Ascent Lending
Program you can do so [HERE](https://partner.ascentfunding.com/savvycoders/)
- N. County WIOA
  - Please Call NorthWest Crossings at 314.615.6010
    - Address is:<br>
Family and Workforce Centers of America<br>
Missouri Job Center<br>
715 Northwest Plaza Drive<br>
St.Ann MO 63074<br>
[Get Directions](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Missouri+Job+Center/@38.7312707,-90.4090319,15z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x87df4a7ba75defab:0x5303aee0dc58e56f!8m2!3d38.731271!4d-90.4002986)<br>
    - Ask for Monica Henderson and explain you are wanting to
see about getting funding for a training program. Savvy
Coders. They will direct you from there.
    - Let us know if you can’t get a hold of anyone or if you
leave a message and no one gets back to you.
